Project Title: Digital Land (App)
1. Introduction
Digital Land is an Android based app for managing Bangladesh's land ownership claims and land disputes. It is made with the vision to change the tedious process and reduce the strugle of regular people. The app is designed to be intuitive, secure and hassle free.

1.1 Purpose
Land services of Bangladesh are more often than not paper-based and requires multiple in person interactions. The purpose of Digi-Land is to digitalize these services. This can reduce discretionary steps and improve trace service delivery. 

1.2 Intended Audience:
This software can be used by any eligible citizen of Bangladesh who owns lands legally. In addition, land office staffs and survey officers for verifying lands can also use this software.
1.3 Intended Use
The system will be used as an online portal for submitting and processing land related requests. Citizens will apply for ownership transfer and track application status. Officials will verify documents and approve or reject requests. The system assists administrative workflow but does not replace legal authority.
